DAZZLING CHIC sat midpack while four wide, and lacked the rally needed. MY EXPRESSION trailed the field into the final turn and passed tiring rival. FLASHY BIZ pressed the pace from a rail position and faltered.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Shirley Vargo H. CENTURY MILE RACE 5 7F Dirt CR: 94. Stakes Purse 50000. A BLACK TYPE HANDICAP STAKE FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE-YEAR-OLDS AND UPWARD. A fee of $100.00 required to nominate. A payment of $500.00 is required to pass the entry box and an additional $400.00 is required to start. The purse will be divided $30,000 t o the owner of the winner, $10,000 to the second place finisher, $5,000 to the third place finisher, $2,500 to the fourth place finisher and $1,000 to the fifth place finisher. A payment of $500.00 will be paid to all horses who start and finish sixth orw orse. High weights preferred. Starters to be named through the entry box by the closing time of entries. The field will be limited to 12 starters. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MINE ME tracked four to five wide, moved up into striking position, waited briefly at the quarter pole, angled out sharply, dug in under steady encouragement to take over deep stretch, and held. PLUM BLUE raced from the back of the pack, was roused through the stretch, and closed gradually to score second honours. TONE IT UP sat in striking distance outside, swung out in the final turn then angled inside under urging, closed gamely for show. PRETTY ARIA saved ground while setting the pace, was under attack at the quarter pole, fought on inside and got caught. FLORAL prompted the pace under a snug hold, fanned three wide in the far turn, and challenge the lead at the quarter pole then flattened out late stretch. DANCE SHOES saved inside, rallied into the lane, and gave way.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: WIDE EYED WILEY settled early, advanced quickly in the final turn then circled into the lane, drifted in under right-handed encouragement, struck the front and held under a late drive. REMAIN CALM unhurried early, went four to five wide into the far turn, closed gamely, and narrowly missed after a determined effort. BRODY'S PAL chased outside, went widest through the final turn, and rallied belatedly to score show. ZURI RISASI chased the pacesetters while five wide, angled to the three path leaving the backstretch, rallied four wide at the quarter pole, was overtaken with a furlong remaining and weakened. CLEVER CONNECTION bid belatedly. SPIRIT RACER broke alertly, contended the lead outside of REFUSE TO TESTIFY, dueled gamely in the final turn and gave way late stretch. PUNCH PERFECT lagged early, and launched a late bid. REFUSE TO TESTIFY sped to the lead away from the gate, dueled inside of SPIRIT RACER, was unable to move on with rival, and yielded. ANTIGUA BAY chased to no avail.
